Event staff scan registrations and distribute lanyards at the entrance, while a welcome announcement outlines the fair schedule over the PA system. Attendees fill interview sign-up sheets and use tablets at kiosks to upload their resumes to the fair database. The atmosphere is enhanced by the aroma of coffee and catered snacks, with small groups quietly rehearsing their elevator pitches against the wall, guided by career counselors. As the event nears its conclusion, volunteers stack collapsed booths and gather leftover brochures, while announcement chimes signal the final hour and attendees exit with tote bags filled with notebooks, pens, and business cards.

Dozens of booths adorned with colorful banners from various companies circle a polished floor, showcasing offerings including glossy case study booklets from consulting firms and demo screens of the latest apps from tech companies. A data science company features a live dashboard reflecting attendance, while a robotics startup utilizes a small drone above its booth to attract attention. Career counselors encourage attendees to maintain eye contact, and HR teams jot notes on tablets during introductions. Groups of friends discuss which recruiters appeared most enthusiastic, marking target employers on their event maps. As students exit, they carry tote bags and stacks of business cards, with the aroma of coffee and catered snacks wafting from the lounge.
